# AI Guidance Rules

For repo AI docs and skill wrappers:

- Read `ai-guidelines/README.md` first.
- Treat `ai-guidelines/` as the canonical source of truth.
- Canonical skill bodies live at `.agents/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`. The `.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` and `.cursor/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` files are thin pointers to the canonical body — never edit them directly.
- Update `ai-guidelines/` before updating wrappers or root docs.
- Use `ai-guidelines/workflows/update-docs.md` and the `prj-sync` skill when refreshing these surfaces.
- Keep the docs aligned with the real integration points: `site.config.json5`, `diagramkit.config.json5`, `content.config.ts`, `schemas/`, `src/entry-server.tsx`, `theme/lib/content.ts`, `scripts/validate.ts`, `scripts/validate-pagesmith.ts`, and `scripts/validate-dist.ts`.
- Keep the repo framed as an `@pagesmith/core` + `diagramkit` site, not an `@pagesmith/docs` site.
- Keep the repo framed primarily as an articles-and-blogs site.
- Treat `projects` as legacy unless the user explicitly asks for project-specific work.
